Here are some common uses of the "static" keyword:

1. **Static Variables**: A static variable is a variable that is shared by all instances of a class. It is initialized only once, when the class is loaded, and retains its value between method calls.

   ```java
public class MyClass {
    public static int count = 0;

    public static void incrementCount() {
        count++;
    }
}
```

2. **Static Methods**: A static method is a method that can be called without creating an instance of the class. It belongs to the class itself, rather than an instance of the class.

   ```java
public class MyClass {
    public static void myMethod() {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
    }
}
```

